IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. CALCULATOR.

DATA DIVISION.
WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-COUNT        PIC S9(9) VALUE 0.
01  WS-REMAINDER    PIC S9(9) VALUE 0.
01  WS-QUOTIENT     PIC S9(9) VALUE 0.
01  WS-PRODUCT      PIC S9(9) VALUE 0.
01  WS-SAVED-A      PIC S9(9) VALUE 0.

LINKAGE SECTION.
COPY CALCULATOR-PARAMS.

PROCEDURE DIVISION USING CALC-PARAMS.
MAIN.
    EVALUATE CALC-OP-CODE
        WHEN 1
            PERFORM ADDITION
        WHEN 2
            PERFORM SUBTRACTION
        WHEN 3
            PERFORM MULTIPLICATION
        WHEN 4
            PERFORM DIVISION-PROC
        WHEN 5
            PERFORM MODULUS
        WHEN OTHER
            MOVE 0 TO CALC-RESULT
    END-EVALUATE
    GOBACK.

ADDITION.
    ADD CALC-A TO CALC-B GIVING CALC-RESULT.

SUBTRACTION.
    SUBTRACT CALC-B FROM CALC-A GIVING CALC-RESULT.

MULTIPLICATION.
    MOVE 0 TO CALC-RESULT.
    PERFORM VARYING WS-COUNT FROM 1 BY 1
            UNTIL WS-COUNT > CALC-B
        ADD CALC-A TO CALC-RESULT
    END-PERFORM.

DIVISION-PROC.
    MOVE 0 TO CALC-RESULT.
    MOVE CALC-A TO WS-REMAINDER.
    PERFORM UNTIL WS-REMAINDER < CALC-B
        SUBTRACT CALC-B FROM WS-REMAINDER
        ADD 1 TO CALC-RESULT
    END-PERFORM.

MODULUS.
    *> Guardar operando A original
    MOVE CALC-A TO WS-SAVED-A

    *> 1. division(a, b) -> cociente en CALC-RESULT
    PERFORM DIVISION-PROC

    *> 2. multiplication(cociente, b) -> producto
    *>    (usa la MULTIPLICATION educativa: suma repetitiva)
    MOVE CALC-RESULT TO CALC-A
    PERFORM MULTIPLICATION

    *> 3. subtraction(a_original, producto) -> resto
    COMPUTE CALC-RESULT = WS-SAVED-A - CALC-RESULT.

END PROGRAM CALCULATOR.
